                    <ab>Appraisement of Mrs. <persName>C. E. Sanders</persName> servants by Two
                        Gentleman <date when="1862-05-02">May 2nd 1862</date></ab>
                    <ab><persName>Theodore Mosher</persName> &amp; <persName>Chas.
                        Digges</persName><lb/> make a copy for <persName>W Snowden</persName></ab>
                </div2>

                <pb xml:id="leaf007r" facs="cww.00616.008.jpg"/>
                <div2 type="section">
                    <dateline><placeName>Washington County, D. C.</placeName><lb/>
                        <date when="1862-05-02">May 2nd 1862</date>.</dateline>
                    <p>We, <persName>Theodore Mosher</persName> &amp; <persName>Charles
                            Digges</persName>, neighbors of Mrs. <persName>Caroline E.
                            Sanders</persName>, having been requested by her to value the within
                        described servants, seventeen in number, her property, &amp; all slaves for
                        life, recently emancipated by an act of Congress approved <date
                            when="1862-04-16">16th April 1862</date>, have fixed the rate and value
                        of each one as set opposite their names, &amp; amounting in the aggregate
                        (for the Seventeen,) to Thirteen Thousand and Six Hundred Dollars</p>
                    <ab>$13,600</ab>
                    <closer><signed><persName>Theodore Mosher</persName>.</signed>
                        <signed><persName>Charles, Digges</persName></signed></closer>
                </div2>

